This paper is primarily focused on networking and wireless communication, which falls under the category of Networked and Distributed Systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses pricing mechanisms and optimization, which could fall under Game Theory (cs.GT) and Learning (cs.LG). The use of crowd-sensing and data aggregation could also be relevant to Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses uncertainty and tradeoffs, which could be relevant to Information Theory (cs.IT).
